{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I rode into Tucson three hours [G7]ago
[C]For supplies and a short friendly game
[G7]Of poker while Smitty put some new shoes
[C]On old Dan before he goes lame
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]I sat in a game at the Miner's Saloon
[C]Soon I had doubled my stake
[G7]The cards run like they'd been dealt by Lady Luck
[C]They were just sealing my fate
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]A young cowboy lost more than he could [C]afford
[F]And accused me of dealing too [C]smart
[F]His draw was too slow and he fell to the [C]floor
[G7]With three bullets close to the [C]heart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Oh cottonwood tree are you waiting for [Em]me
[Dm]Waiting to take me [C]away
[F]I've done no wrong but the town cannot [C]see
[G7]And so with my life I must [C]pay
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[G7]A crowd started gathering the sheriff came in
[C]I handed him over my gun
[G7]Was then when I found out the boy I had killed
[C]Was the town's biggest man's only son
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[G7]I tried to explain I had shot in defense
[C]It was the young cowboy or me
[G7]The crowd wouldn't listen so they drug me out
[C]To the limb of this cottonwood tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[G7]Majestically standing out here all alone
[C]It's spring and the valley is green
[G7]But I can't admire a place I don't belong
[C]To me it's all like a bad dream
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[F]But old Dan's beneath me with new shows and [C]all
[F]As they place the noose round my [C]neck
[F]Cowboys I've never laid eyes on [C]before
[G7]Are tying my hands to my [C]back
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Oh cottonwood tree are you waiting for [Em]me
[Dm]Waiting to take me [C]away
[F]I've done no wrong but the town cannot [C]see
[G7]And so with my life I must [C]pay
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
[G7]I see hate in the eyes of the town's biggest man
[C]As he pulls a branch from the tree
[G7]To whip the backside of my old pony Dan
[C]So he'll run out from under me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
[G7]Insane he won't listen to my last appeal
[C]A wild grin has covered his face
[G7]As I tried to reason just how he would feel
[C]If he were up here in my place
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 11}
[G7]There's many a mountain trail I'll never ride
[C]Green valleys I'll never see
[G7]A young cowboy died and a man's foolish pride
[C]Brought me to this cottonwood tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 12}
[F]My face is turned upward and I cannot [C]breathe
[F]The sky's growing dark [C]overhead
[F]The knot's pulling tight as my body sweeps [C]free
[G7]A few moments more I'll be [C]dead
{end_of_verse}

